com.studiomediatech.queryresponse

Class ChainingResponseBuilder<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.studiomediatech.queryresponse.ChainingResponseBuilder<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of response entries or elements.

    public class ChainingResponseBuilder<T>
extends Object
    Providing the entry-point to the fluid builder for responses, through the respondTo(String, Class) method.

    Building a response instance will start a long running query consumer which will respond to any matching queries, for as long as the service is running.

      • withSink

        protected ChainingResponseBuilder<T> withSink(Consumer<ChainingResponseBuilder<T>> sink)
        Replaces the current sink for this builder, effectively removing the registry and instead making the terminal operation to apply the builder on the given sink. For example: 
                AtomicReference<ResponseBuilder<String>> capture = new AtomicReference<>(null);

        ResponseBuilder.respondTo("foobar")
            .withSink(capture::set)
            .withAll()
            .from("hello", "world!");

        assertThat(capture.get()).isNotNull();

        This method is protected, in order to reduce visibility and only make it available to tests.

        Parameters:
        sink - to consume this builder, in the terminal operation call to any from(...) method.
        Returns:
        this builder, for chaining.
